dia.org/wiki/Shiloh_Church"}
{"title_page": "Maryland Route 331", "text_new": "{{About|the current Maryland Route 331|the former highway|Maryland Route 331 (former)}}\n{{Infobox road\n|state=MD\n|type=MD\n|route=331\n|name=\n|alternate_name=\n|name_notes=\n|section=\n|marker_image=\n|map_alt=\n|map=Maryland Route 331 map.png\n|map_notes=\n|length_mi=28.74\n|length_round=2\n|length_ref=<ref name=MarylandHLR>{{Maryland HLR|year=2013|county1=Dorchester|county2=Caroline|county3=Talbot|accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref>\n|length_notes=\n|tourist=[[File:MUTCD D6-4.svg|20px|alt=|link=]] [[Harriet Tubman Underground Railroad Byway (Maryland)|Harriet Tubman Underground Railroad Byway]]<br>[[File:MD scenic byway.svg|20px|alt=|link=]] [[Chesapeake Country Scenic Byway]]\n|established=1939\n|decommissioned=\n|maint=[[Maryland State Highway Administration|MDSHA]]\n|direction_a=South\n|terminus_a={{jct|state=MD|US|50}} in [[Vienna, Maryland|Vienna]]\n|junction={{jct|state=MD|MD|14}} in [[Rhodesdale, Maryland|Rhodesdale]]<br/>\n{{jct|state=MD|MD|392}} in [[Hurlock, Maryland|Hurlock]]<br/>\n{{jct|state=MD|MD|307}} in Hurlock<br/>\n{{jct|state=MD|MD|16}} near Hurlock<br/>\n{{jct|state=MD|MD|318}} in [[Linchester, Maryland|Linchester]]<br/>\n{{jct|state=MD|MD|817}} in Linchester<br/>\n{{jct|state=MD|MD|16}} in [[Preston, Maryland|Preston]]<br/>\n{{jct|state=MD|MD|578}} in [[Bethlehem, Maryland|Bethlehem]]\n|direction_b=North\n|terminus_b={{jct|state=MD|US|50}} in [[Easton, Maryland|Easton]]\n|cities=\n|counties=[[Dorchester County, Maryland|Dorchester]], [[Caroline County, Maryland|Caroline]], [[Talbot County, Maryland|Talbot]]\n|system=\n|previous_type=MD\n|previous_route=330\n|next_type=MD\n|next_route=332\n|browse=\n}}\n\n'''Maryland Route 331''' ('''MD 331''') is a {{convert|28.74|mi|km|2|adj=on}} [[state highway]] on the [[Maryland Eastern Shore|Eastern Shore]] of [[Maryland]] in the [[United States]]. The route runs from [[Vienna, Maryland|Vienna]] in [[Dorchester County, Maryland|Dorchester County]] northwest to [[Easton, Maryland|Easton]] in [[Talbot County, Maryland|Talbot County]], intersecting [[U.S. Route 50 in Maryland|U.S. Route 50]] (US 50) at both ends. MD 331 is a two-lane undivided road most of its length that passes mostly through agricultural areas. The road also passes through the communities of [[Hurlock, Maryland|Hurlock]] and [[Preston, Maryland|Preston]] along the way. It encounters several routes during its journey, including [[Maryland Route 14|MD 14]] near [[Rhodesdale, Maryland|Rhodesdale]] and [[Maryland Route 16|MD 16]] in the Preston area, both of which the route forms [[concurrency (road)|concurrencies]] with. In addition, the route also intersects with [[Maryland Route 392|MD 392]] and [[Maryland Route 307|MD 307]] in Hurlock and with [[Maryland Route 318|MD 318]] near Preston.\n\nMost of present-day MD 331 was designated as part of [[U.S. Route 213|US 213]] in 1926 when the [[U.S. Highway System]] was established. By 1940, US 213 was moved to a new alignment that crossed the [[Choptank River]] at [[Cambridge, Maryland|Cambridge]] on a bridge built in 1935 and MD 331 was designated to run from Vienna to Easton. Both ends of MD 331 have been shortened since, with the southernmost portion of MD 331 curtailed following the completion of the US 50 bypass of Vienna by the 1990s and the northern terminus of the route cut back to US 50 in 2004 when the state-maintained portion of Dover Road to Dover Street in Easton was turned over to the city.\n\n==Route description==\nMD 331 is a part of the [[National Highway System (United States)|National Highway System]] as a principal arterial within the town of Easton.<ref name=\"MarylandHLR\"/><ref name=\"National Highway System\">{{cite map|publisher=Federal Highway Administration|title=National Highway System: Maryland|url=http://www.fhwa.dot.gov/planning/national_highway_system/nhs_maps/maryland/md_maryland.pdf|date=October 1, 2012|section=|format=PDF|accessdate=2015-02-09}}</ref>\n\n===Dorchester County===\n[[File:MD 16-MD 331 Preston shields.jpg|thumb|left|Shields for MD 16 and MD 331 in Preston]]MD 331 begins at an interchange with [[U.S. Route 50 in Maryland|US 50]] (Ocean Gateway) in [[Vienna, Maryland|Vienna]], [[Dorchester County, Maryland|Dorchester County]], a short distance west of the [[Nanticoke River]]. MD 331 signage continues south of US 50 on county-maintained Rhodesdale Vienna Road to an intersection with Old Ocean Gateway in Vienna. From this interchange, the route heads north on Rhodesdale Vienna Road, a two-lane undivided road.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\">{{google maps |url=https://maps.google.com/maps?f=d&source=s_d&saddr=US+50+and+MD+331+vienna,+md&daddr=38.646372,-75.892181+to:US+50+and+MD+331+easton,+md&geocode=&hl=en&mra=dpe&mrcr=0&mrsp=1&sz=11&via=1&sll=38.622235,-75.883942&sspn=0.237116,0.439453&ie=UTF8&ll=38.671573,-75.952606&spn=0.473905,0.878906&t=h&z=10 |title=overview of Maryland Route 331 |accessdate=2009-04-29}}</ref> It passes through wooded areas, with a set of [[power line]]s and an abandoned railroad right-of-way owned by [[Delmarva Power|Delmarva Power and Light Company]] located along the east side of the road.<ref name=\"google\"/> MD 331 continues into farmland, with some rural residences alongside the road, before it approaches [[Reids Grove, Maryland|Reids Grove]], where [[Maryland Route 819|MD 819]] (Reids Grove Road) loops to the west of MD 331.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/> Past Reids Grove, the route continues through a mix of woodland and farmland, still paralleling the power lines and the abandoned railroad.<ref name=\"google\"/> \n\n[[File:2017-08-21 10 47 01 View north along Maryland State Route 331 (Shiloh Church Hurlock Road) at Maryland State Route 14 (Railroad Avenue) in Petersburg, Dorchester County, Maryland.jpg|thumb|right|View north along MD 331 at MD 16 near Petersburg]]\nMD 331 reaches [[Rhodesdale, Maryland|Rhodesdale]], where it intersects [[Maryland Route 14|MD 14]] (Rhodesdale Eldorado Road). At this intersection, the route makes a left turn to run [[concurrency (road)|concurrent]] with MD 14 along East New Market Rhodesdale Road, heading west through Rhodesdale. The road leaves Rhodesdale and heads into farmland. MD 331 splits from MD 14 in Shiloh Church by turning north on Shiloh Church Hurlock Road at an intersection.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/> Along Shiloh Church Hurlock Road, MD 331 passes a few residences before heading through more farm fields.<ref name=\"google\"/>\n\nMD 331 enters [[Hurlock, Maryland|Hurlock]] and heads into residential areas, with the name changing to Main Street at the Jackson Street intersection. It passes more residences before intersecting [[Maryland Route 392|MD 392]] (Delaware Avenue). Past MD 392, the road passes more homes before it heads into the downtown area of Hurlock, where it crosses the [[Maryland and Delaware Railroad]]'s Seaford Line and [[Maryland Route 307|MD 307]] (Broad Street). Past this intersection, MD 331 heads northwest on Academy Street past numerous homes before the road leaves Hurlock. Upon leaving Hurlock, the road becomes Waddells Corner Road and it heads into farmland.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/> The road turns to the west and continues through agricultural areas with intermittent residences.<ref name=\"google\"/> It comes to an intersection with [[Maryland Route 16|MD 16]] (East New Market Ellwood Road), where MD 331 makes a right turn to head north along with MD 16.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/> MD 16 and MD 331 head north through a mix of woods and farms with some residences. The road continues through rural areas with an increasing number of residences as it approaches the [[Preston, Maryland|Preston]] area. The road intersects the western terminus of [[Maryland Route 318|MD 318]] (Preston Road) near businesses. Past this intersection, MD 16 and MD 331 continue northwest on Preston Road.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/>\n\n===Caroline and Talbot counties===\n[[File:US 50 EB at MD 331 Easton.JPG|thumb|left|The northern terminus of MD 331 in Easton as viewed from eastbound US 50]]The road crosses the Hunting Creek into [[Caroline County, Maryland|Caroline County]]. In [[Linchester, Maryland|Linchester]], [[Maryland Route 817|MD 817]] loops off to the west of MD 16 and MD 331 on Linchester Road. Past MD 817, the road enters Preston, where it becomes Main Street, passing by residences and some businesses. The route intersects [[Maryland Route 324|MD 324]] (Maple Avenue) before reaching the center of town, where MD 16 splits from MD 331 by heading northeast on Harmony Road. Past this intersection, the route passes more residences before leaving Preston, where it becomes Dover Bridge Road.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/>  It heads north into rural areas of woods and farms with some residences along the road.<ref name=\"google\"/> The road turns to the northwest and intersects Tanyard Road. MD 331 turns west and continues to the residential community of [[Bethlehem, Maryland|Bethlehem]], where it intersects [[Maryland Route 578|MD 578]] (Bethlehem Road). Past Bethlehem, the road continues past many rural residences.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/>\n\nMD 331 enters wetlands as it approaches the [[Choptank River]], which it crosses into [[Talbot County, Maryland|Talbot County]] on the [[Dover Bridge]], a high-level bridge. Upon entering Talbot County, the route becomes Dover Road and continues to the northwest through a mix of woodland and farmland.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/>  It turns to the west with the number of residences increasing as it approaches [[Easton, Maryland|Easton]].<ref name=\"google\"/>  Upon reaching Easton, MD 331 heads into commercial and industrial areas. The route ends at the intersection with US 50 (Ocean Gateway), where Dover Road continues west as a local road toward downtown Easton.<ref name=MarylandHLR/><ref name=\"google\"/>\n\n==History==\nMD 331 from Rhodesdale to Easton was one of the original state roads marked for improvement in 1909.  In 1910, the only paved sections of the highway were the approaches to Dover Bridge in both Talbot County and Caroline County.<ref name=\"1910 map\"/>  The state road was paved from Hurlock to Shiloh Church in 1912, from Easton to Waddell's Corner in 1913 and 1914, from Waddell's Corner to Hurlock in 1915, and within Hurlock in 1916.<ref name=\"1915 src report\"/><ref name=\"1919 src report\"/>  When the U.S. Highway System was organized in 1926, the state road became part of US 213.<ref name=\"1927 map\"/><ref name=\"1926 US Highway Map\"/>\n\nThe first section of the Vienna&ndash;Rhodesdale highway was {{convert|2|mi|km}} of pavement south from Rhodesdale that was completed by 1923.<ref name=\"1923 map\"/>  The remainder of the highway was under construction by 1924, with another {{convert|2|mi|km}} section of the road completed north from Vienna by 1927.<ref name=\"1927 map\"/><ref name=\"1926 src report\"/>  The gap between Vienna and Rhodesdale was filled in 1928.<ref name=\"1928 map\"/>  When the Nanticoke River Bridge at Vienna was completed in 1931, US 213 was rerouted between Mardela Springs and Rhodesdale to pass through Vienna.<ref name=\"1934 src report\"/><ref name=\"1933 map\"/>  A new Dover Bridge, replacing a bridge built in the 19th century, was completed in 1932.<ref name=\"1934 src report\"/><ref name=\"NBI Dover Bridge\"/><ref name=\"Dover Bridges\"/>  In 1939, the original MD 331 and US 213 swapped routes; US 213 also assumed MD 344 between Vienna and MD 16 at Mount Holly.<ref name=\"1939 map\"/>\n\nMD 331 has seen little change since 1939.  MD 331 and MD 16 were realigned around Ellwood and Linchester around 1960.<ref name=\"NBI Hunting Creek\"/><ref name=\"1960 map\"/>  MD 331's southern terminus was truncated at its newly constructed interchange with US 50 in Vienna in 1991 shortly after US 50 bypassed Vienna.<ref name=\"1991 map\"/>  MD 331's northern terminus has been rolled back twice in Easton.  The state highway was rolled back from Washington Street to Park Street in 1983.<ref name=\"1983 map\"/>  MD 331 was truncated at US 50 in 2004.<ref name=MarylandHLR2004/> On October 14, 2014, groundbreaking for a new Dover Bridge took place, with Lieutenant Governor [[Anthony G. Brown]] and other state and local politicians in attendance. The new bridge, which was built to the south of the swing bridge, was constructed as a fixed-span steel girder bridge.<ref name=stardem/> Construction on the new Dover Bridge cost $64 million.<ref name=stardem/><ref name=SHADoverBridge/> The new bridge opened to traffic on June 12, 2018.<ref name=wboc/> A ribbon-cutting ceremony for the new Dover Bridge was held on June 13, 2018, with Governor [[Larry Hogan]] and other state and local officials in attendance.<ref name=stardem2/>\n\n==Junction list==\n{{jcttop|length_ref=<br><ref name=MarylandHLR />|state=MD}}\n{{MDint\n|county=Dorchester\n|cspan=9\n|location=Vienna\n|mile=0.00\n|road={{jct|state=MD|US|50|name1=Ocean Gateway|city1=Cambridge|city2=Bay Bridge|city3=Salisbury|city4=Ocean City}}\n|notes=Interchange; southern terminus of MD 331\n}}\n{{MDint\n|location=Reids Grove\n|lspan=2\n|mile=2.73\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|819|dir1=north|name1=Reids Grove Road}}\n|notes=Southern terminus of MD 819\n}}\n{{MDint\n|mile=2.90\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|819|dir1=south|name1=Reids Grove Road}}\n|notes=Northern terminus of MD 819\n}}\n{{MDint\n|location=Rhodesdale\n|mile=5.92\n|type=concur\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|14|dir1=east|name1=Rhodesdale Eldorado Road|to2=to|MD|313|dir2=north|city1=Brookview}}\n|notes=South end of MD 14 overlap\n}}\n{{MDint\n|location=Shiloh Church\n|mile=7.96\n|type=concur\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|14|dir1=west|name1=East New Market Rhodesdale Road|location1=[[North Dorchester High School|North Dorchester School Complex]]|city2=East New Market}}\n|notes=North end of MD 14 overlap\n}}\n{{MDint\n|location=Hurlock\n|lspan=2\n|mile=10.91\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|392|name1=Delaware Avenue|to2=to|MD|307}}\n|notes=\n}}\n{{MDint\n|mile=11.37\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|307|dir1=north|name1=Broad Street}}\n|notes=Southern terminus of MD 307\n}}\n{{MDint\n|location=none\n|mile=13.82\n|type=concur\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|16|dir1=west|name1=East New Market Ellwood Road|city1=East New Market}}\n|notes=South end of MD 16 overlap\n}}\n{{MDint\n|location=Linchester\n|lspan=2\n|mile=17.14\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|318|dir1=east|name1=Preston Road|city1=Federalsburg}}\n|notes=Western terminus of MD 318\n}}\n{{MDint\n|county=Caroline\n|cspan=5\n|mile=17.36\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|817|dir1=north|name1=Linchester Road}}\n|notes=Southern terminus of MD 817; officially MD 817A\n}}\n{{MDint\n|location=Preston\n|lspan=3\n|mile=17.78\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|817|dir1=south|name1=Linchester Road}}\n|notes=Northern terminus of MD 817; officially MD 817A\n}}\n{{MDint\n|mile=18.33\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|324|dir1=south|name1=Maple Avenue|city1=Choptank}}\n|notes=Northern terminus of MD 324\n}}\n{{MDint\n|mile=18.40\n|type=concur \n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|16|dir1=east|name1=Harmony Road|city1=Harmony|city2=Denton}}\n|notes=North end of MD 16 overlap\n}}\n{{MDint\n|location=Bethlehem\n|mile=21.81\n|road={{jct|state=MD|MD|578|dir1=north|name1=Bethlehem Road|city1=Harmony}}\n|notes=Southern terminus of MD 578\n}}\n{{jctbridge\n|river=[[Choptank River]]\n|mile=24.78\n|line=yes\n|bridge=[[Dover Bridge]]\n}}\n{{MDint\n|county=Talbot\n|location=Easton\n|mile=28.74\n|road={{jct|state=MD|US|50|name1=Ocean Gateway}}\n|notes=Northern terminus of MD 331\n}}\n{{jctbtm|keys=concur}}\n\n==Auxiliary routes==\n*MD 331A is the designation for the {{convert|0.08|mi|km|adj=on}} section of Linchester Road from MD 331 to MD 817A near Preston in Caroline County.<ref name=MarylandHLR/>\n*MD 331B is the designation for the {{convert|0.06|mi|km|adj=on}} section of Seaman Road from MD 331 near its intersection with MD 318 in Dorchester County to Langrell Road (MD 817B) on the Dorchester/Caroline County line near Preston.<ref name=MarylandHLR/>\n*MD 331D is the designation for the {{convert|0.21|mi|km|adj=on}} section of Payne Road from MD 331 to the terminus of County Route 201 southeast of Preston.<ref name=MarylandHLR/>\n\n==See also==\n*{{Portal-inline|Maryland Roads}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"1934 src report\">{{cite journal|title=Report of the State Roads Commission of Maryland|volume=1931-1934|pages=19, 41, 46|publisher=Maryland State Roads Commission|location=Baltimore|date=1934-12-28|url=https://archive.org/details/reportofstateroa1931mary|accessdate=2010-10-05}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"1910 map\">{{cite map|publisher=Maryland Geological Survey|title=Map of Maryland|edition=1910|section=}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"1927 map\">{{cite map|publisher=Maryland Geological Survey|title=Map of Maryland: Showing State Road System and State Aid Roads|edition=1927|section=}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"1915 src report\">{{cite journal|title=Report of the State Roads Commission of Maryland|volume=1912-1915|pages=108, 110, 114, 124, 126|publisher=Maryland State Roads Commission|location=Baltimore|date=May 1915|url=https://archive.org/details/annualreportsofs1912mary|accessdate=2010-10-05}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"1919 src report\">{{cite journal|title=Report of the State Roads Commission of Maryland|volume=1916-1919|pages=48, 52|publisher=Maryland State Roads Commission|location=Baltimore|date=January 1920|url=https://archive.org/details/annualreportsofs1916mary|accessdate=2010-10-05}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"1926 US Highway Map\">{{cite map |author1= [[Bureau of Public Roads]] |author2= [[American Association of State Highway Officials]] |date= November 11, 1926 |title= United States System of Highways Adopted for Uniform Marking by the American Association of State Highway Officials |url= http://texashistory.unt.edu/ark:/67531/metapth298433/m1/1/zoom/ |sca